cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC

This paper deals with the design of a language that enforces obliviousness, which is a property of secure computation. The paper focuses on probabilistic algorithms, which are commonly used in cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also introduces a new type system, which is a core feature of programming languages, so cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another likely category. The paper discusses the implementation of data structures, such as stacks and queues, which are part of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of regions, which is a concept related to logic and semantics, so cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the language, which is related to computational complexity, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category.
